{"title": "Anton 2: Raising the Bar for Performance and Programmability in a Special-Purpose Molecular Dynamics Supercomputer.", "fields": ["supercomputer", "molecular dynamics", "computation", "scalability", "architecture"], "abstract": "Anton 2 is a second-generation special-purpose supercomputer for molecular dynamics simulations that achieves significant gains in performance, programmability, and capacity compared to its predecessor, Anton 1. The architecture of Anton 2 is tailored for fine-grained event-driven operation, which improves performance by increasing the overlap of computation with communication, and also allows a wider range of algorithms to run efficiently, enabling many new software-based optimizations. A 512-node Anton 2 machine, currently in operation, is up to ten times faster than Anton 1 with the same number of nodes, greatly expanding the reach of all-atom bio molecular simulations. Anton 2 is the first platform to achieve simulation rates of multiple microseconds of physical time per day for systems with millions of atoms. Demonstrating strong scaling, the machine simulates a standard 23,558-atom benchmark system at a rate of 85 \u00b5s/day -- 180 times faster than any commodity hardware platform or general-purpose supercomputer.", "citation": "Citations (122)", "year": "2014", "departments": ["Columbia University", "D. E. Shaw Research", "D. E. Shaw Research", "D. E. Shaw Research", "D. E. Shaw Research"], "conf": "sc", "authors": ["David E. Shaw.....http://dblp.org/pers/hd/s/Shaw:David_E=", "J. P. Grossman.....http://dblp.org/pers/hd/g/Grossman:J=_P=", "Joseph A. Bank.....http://dblp.org/pers/hd/b/Bank:Joseph_A=", "Brannon Batson.....http://dblp.org/pers/hd/b/Batson:Brannon", "J. Adam Butts.....http://dblp.org/pers/hd/b/Butts:J=_Adam", "Jack C. Chao.....http://dblp.org/pers/hd/c/Chao:Jack_C=", "Martin M. Deneroff.....http://dblp.org/pers/hd/d/Deneroff:Martin_M=", "Ron O. Dror.....http://dblp.org/pers/hd/d/Dror:Ron_O=", "Amos Even.....http